1746879680349679623%3Fref_src%3Dtwsrc%255Etfw%5C%22%3EJanuary%2015%2C%202024%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Fblockquote%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EJaishankar%20pointed%20that%20there%20had%20been%20attacks%20near%20the%20Indian%20coast%20as%20part%20of%20the%20increased%20threats%20against%20maritime%20commercial%20traffic%20in%20that%20section%20of%20the%20Indian%20Ocean.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EStating%20that%20it%20was%20a%20%E2%80%9Cmatter%20of%20great%20concern%20to%20the%20international%20community%E2%80%9D%2C%20Jaishankar%20said%2C%20%E2%80%9CObviously%2C%20it%20also%20has%20a%20direct%20bearing%20on%20India%E2%80%99s%20energy%20and%20economic%20interests.%20This%20fraught%20situation%20is%20not%20to%20the%20benefit%20of%20any%20party%2C%20and%20this%20must%20be%20clearly%20recognised%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20attacks%20by%20the%20US-led%20group%20against%20Houthi%20centres%20in%20Yemen%20was%20not%20mentioned%20in%20the%20public%20statements.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20stating%20that%20Tehran%20also%20wanted%20to%20ensure%20secure%20shipping%20lines%2C%20Amir-Abdollahian%20mentioned%20that%20a%20senior%20Yemeni%20official%20had%20committed%20during%20a%20visit%20to%20Iran%20two%20weeks%20ago%20that%20it%20would%20not%20disrupt%20the%20movement%20of%20merchant%20ships.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Iranian%20minister%2C%20however%2C%20added%20that%20the%20Yemeni%20official%20also%20said%20that%20they%20would%20stop%20the%20passage%20of%20Israel-linked%20or%20Israel-bound%20ships%20as%20long%20as%20the%20war%20in%20Gaza%20continued%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.irna.ir%2Fnews%2F85355236%2FIran-FM-hails-SCO-BRICS-role-in-Tehran-New-Delhi-cooperation%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ethe%20state-run%20news%20agency%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIRNA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20reported%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EGaza%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESpeaking%20on%20the%20Gaza%20conflict%2C%20Jaishankar%20reiterated%20that%20India%20had%20an%20%E2%80%9Cuncompromising%E2%80%9D%20position%20against%20terrorism%2C%20but%20that%20loss%20of%20civilian%20life%20had%20to%20be%20avoided.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CThe%20deeply%20concerning%20situation%20in%20Gaza%20was%20naturally%20a%20subject%20of%20our%20discussions.%20The%20loss%20of%20civilian%20lives%2C%20especially%20that%20of%20women%20and%20children%20was%20our%20primary%20focus.%20There%20is%20a%20visible%20humanitarian%20crisis%20that%20needs%20to%20be%20addressed%20and%20the%20creation%20of%20sustainable%20humanitarian%20corridors%20is%20the%20need%20of%20the%20day%2C%E2%80%9D%20the%20Indian%20minister%20noted.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIndia%20is%20among%20the%20few%20nations%20in%20the%20Global%20South%20that%20has%20refrained%20from%20explicitly%20advocating%20for%20a%20ceasefire%2C%20despite%20casting%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Findia-votes-in-favour-of-unga-resolution-calling-for-immediate-ceasefire-in-gaza%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efavourable%20vote%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20the%20most%20recent%20UN%20General%20Assembly%20resolution%20that%20urged%20the%20cessation%20of%20violence.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20Indian%20minister%20also%20referred%20to%20India%E2%80%99s%20support%20for%20a%20%E2%80%9Ctwo-state%20solution%2C%20where%20the%20Palestinian%20people%20are%20able%20to%20live%20freely%20in%20an%20independent%20country%20within%20secure%20borders%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CI%20stressed%20on%20the%20need%20for%20all%20parties%20to%20avoid%20provocative%20and%20escalatory%20actions%2C%20and%20to%20facilitate%20movement%20towards%20dialogue%20and%20diplomacy%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWith%20connectivity%20high%20on%20the%20agenda%2C%20Jaishankar%20asserted%20that%20India%20wanted%20to%20benefit%20from%20Iran%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Cunique%20geographical%20position%20to%20access%20markets%20in%20Central%20Asia%2C%20Afghanistan%20and%20Eurasia%E2%80%9D.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EChabahar%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20calling%20for%20re-energising%20the%20International%20North%20South%20Transport%20Corridor%2C%20the%20Indian%20minister%20also%20reiterated%20New%20Delhi%E2%80%99s%20commitment%20to%20developing%20the%20Iranian%20port%20of%20Chabahar.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%E2%80%9CGiven%20the%20importance%20of%20this%20project%20for%20both%20nations%2C%20I%20emphasised%20the%20need%20to%20monitor%20its%20progress%20under%20the%20direct%20supervision%20of%20the%20political%20leadership%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EHe%20also%20indicated%20that%20discussions%20were%20held%20on%20the%20draft%20agreement%20on%20Chabahar%20which%20will%20talk%20about%20India%E2%80%99s%20involvement%20in%20the%20port%20for%20next%20ten%20years.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhile%20the%20Indian%20minister%20only%20referred%20to%20discussions%2C%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ci%3E%3Cspan%3EIRNA%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fi%3E%3Cspan%3E%20said%20that%20the%20text%20was%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fen.irna.ir%2Fnews%2F85355146%2FIran-India-reach-agreement-on-developing-Chabahar-port%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Efinalised%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20during%20Jaishankar%E2%80%99s%20meeting%20with%20Iranian%20transport%20minister%20Mehrdad%20Bazrpash.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAfter%20the%20meeting%20at%20the%20foreign%20ministry%2C%20Jaishankar%20also%20called%20on%20Iranian%20President%20Ebrahim%20Raisi.%C2%A0%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cblockquote%20class%3D%5C%22twitter-tweet%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cp%20dir%3D%5C%22ltr%5C%22%20lang%3D%5C%22en%5C%22%3EHonoured%20to