0City.%20The%20award%20only%20covered%20the%20period%20after%20Messi%20had%20led%20Argentina%20to%20World%20Cup%20glory%20in%20December%202022%20to%20August%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDuring%20that%20time%20the%20eight-time%20Ballon%20d'Or%20winner%20had%20a%20subdued%20end%20to%20his%20career%20at%20Paris%20Saint-Germain%2C%20despite%20winning%20the%20Ligue%201%20title%2C%20before%20joining%20MLS%20side%20Inter%20Miami%20in%20June.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMessi%20quickly%20made%20his%20mark%20in%20the%20United%20States%20as%20he%20helped%20the%20franchise%2C%20part-owned%20by%20David%20Beckham%2C%20to%20their%20first%20trophy%20by%20winning%20the%20Leagues%20Cup%20in%20August.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHaaland%20was%20favourite%20to%20win%20after%20scoring%2052%20times%20in%20his%20debut%20season%20with%20City%20as%20the%20English%20side%20won%20a%20treble%20of%20Champions%20League%2C%20Premier%20League%20and%20FA%20Cup.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20receiving%20the%20same%20number%20of%20points%20from%20a%20scoring%20system%20based%20off%20votes%20from%20national%20team%20captains%2C%20coaches%2C%20journalists%20and%20fans%2C%20Messi%20was%20crowned%20victor%20thanks%20to%20more%20first-choice%20nominations.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMessi's%20former%20club%20teammate%20Kylian%20Mbappe%20was%20third.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20all%20three%20of%20the%20men's%20finalists%20did%20not%20attend%20the%20ceremony%20leaving%20Arsenal%20and%20France%20legend%20Thierry%20Henry%2C%20who%20was%20co-hosting%20the%20event%2C%20to%20pick%20up%20the%20award%20in%20Messi's%20absence.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E-%20'Powerful%20generation%20of%20women'%20-%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBonmati's%20selection%20as%20the%20best%20women's%20player%20was%20never%20in%20doubt%20as%20she%20completed%20a%20clean%20sweep%20of%20personal%20awards%20after%20helping%20Spain%20to%20win%20the%20World%20Cup%20and%20Barcelona%20to%20Champions%20League%20glory%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%202