l%E2%80%99s%202023%20report%20concludes.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThat%20means%20issues%20such%20as%20hunger%20in%20Angola%2C%20chronic%20malnutrition%20in%20Burundi%20and%20high%20child%20mortality%20in%20the%20Central%20African%20Republic%20are%20disappearing%20from%20public%20view%2C%20the%20authors%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAnalyst%20Fredson%20Guilengue%20from%20the%20Rosa%20Luxemburg%20Foundation%20in%20Johannesburg%20sees%20reasons%20for%20the%20low%20interest%20in%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20plight%20in%20the%20escalation%20of%20the%20two%20conflicts%20in%20the%20West.%20%E2%80%9CThe%20first%20is%20the%20continuation%20of%20the%20Russia-Ukraine%20war.%20It%20is%20getting%20a%20lot%20of%20attention%20worldwide%2C%20especially%20on%20the%20European%20continent%2C%20because%20the%20war%20is%20returning%20to%20Europe%2C%E2%80%9D%20Guilengue%20told%20%3Cem%3EDW.%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20global%20media%20is%20now%20focusing%20more%20on%20Europe%20and%20less%20on%20Africa%20or%20other%20places.%20This%20will%20continue%20in%202024%20as%20the%20wars%20continue.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20the%20second%20trouble%20spot%2C%20namely%20the%20conflict%20between%20Israel%20and%20Hamas%20in%20Gaza%2C%20has%20exacerbated%20this%20dilemma%3A%20what%20is%20happening%20in%20other%20parts%20of%20the%20world%20hardly%20receives%20any%20attention.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20current%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.care.de%2Fschwerpunkte%2Fnothilfe%2Fvergessene-krisen%2F%5C%22%3E%20%E2%80%9CBreaking%20the%20Silence%E2%80%9D%20report%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20the%20aid%20organisation%20draws%20attention%20to%20the%20%E2%80%9Cforgotten%20crises%E2%80%9D%20for%20the%20eighth%20time.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEvery%20year%2C%20Care%20lists%20the%20ten%20humanitarian%20emergencies%20in%20the%20world%20that%20have%20hardly%20been%20reported.%20In%202023%20and%202022%2C%20they%20all%20took%20place%20in%20Africa%2C%20led%20in%20the%20second%20year%20by%20Angola.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHowever%2C%20the%20Central%20African%20Republic%20occupied%20a%20place%20in%20this%20sad%20list%20every%20year%2C%20emphasised%20David%20Mutua%2C%20Care%20spokesperson%20for%20the%20African%20regions.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAngola%20in%20extreme%20distress%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20aid%20organisation%20commissioned%20the%20media%20monitoring%20service%20Meltwater%20to%20examine%20five%20million%20online%20articles%20in%20Arabic%2C%20German%2C%20English%2C%20French%20and%20Spanish%20from%20January%201%20to%20September%2030%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFrom%20a%20list%20of%2048%20humanitarian%20crises%20affecting%20more%20than%20one%20million%20people%20the%20ten%20crises%20with%20the%20lowest%20media%20presence%20were%20identified.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOnly%2077%2C000%20of%20the%20articles%20analyzed%20dealt%20with%20Africa%E2%80%99s%20humanitarian%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fworld-bank-extreme-poverty-here-to-stay%2Fa-63346922%5C%22%3Edisasters%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20in%20contrast%20to%20the%20new%20Barbie%20film%2C%20which%20topped%20the%20list%20with%20273%2C279%20publications%2C%20Care%20Africa%20spokesperson%20Mutua%20said%20at%20the%20presentation%20of%20the%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAngola%20accounted%20for%20just%20under%201%2C000%20publications%2C%20although%20drought%2C%20flooding%20and%20hunger%20meant%20that%20more%20than%20seven%20million%20people%20needed%20humanitarian%20aid%20in%202023.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAngolans%20have%20been%20struggling%20with%20drought%20for%2040%20years%2C%20there%20is%20a%20lack%20of%20clean%20drinking%20water%20and%20almost%20thirty%20years%20of%20civil%20war%20(1975%20to%202002)%20have%20left%20a%20country%20littered%20with%20mines.%20Although%20it%20is%20rich%20in%20oil%20and%20diamonds%2C%20most%20of%20the%20approximately%2037%20million%20Angolans%20live%20in%20poverty.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EClimate%20change%20drives%20crises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20second%20place%20is%20Zambia%2C%20where%201.35%20million%20people%20are%20affected%20by%20hunger.%20The%20country%20is%20suffering%20greatly%20from%20the%20consequences%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fel-nino-2023-on-track-to-be-hottest-year-ever-on-record%2Fa-66504033%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESo%2C%20too%2C%20is%20Burundi%20where%20the%20population%20regularly%20battles%20floods.%20Almost%2070%2C000%20people%20have%20been%20displaced%20as%20a%20result%2C%20and%20almost%205.6%20million%20children%20in%20the%20small%20East%20African%20country%20are%20chronically%20malnourished.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20many%20people%20in%20Senegal%20and%20Mauritania%20also%20also%20suffer%20from%20hunger.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20impact%20of%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fclimate-change-exacerbating-conflict-and-poverty-imf%2Fa-66668775%5C%22%3Eclimate%20change%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%20people%20and%20food%20security%20is%20serious%20and%20largely%20avoidable.%20%E2%80%9CClimate%20change%20drives%20famine%2C%20it%20makes%20water%20problems%20worse%2C%20it%20destroys%20people%E2%80%99s%20habitats%20and%20drives%20them%20out%20of%20their%20homes%2C%20it%20prevents%20children%20from%20going%20to%20school%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Deepmala%20Mahla%2C%20Care%E2%80%99s%20Director%20for%20Humanitarian%20Aid.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20consequences%20are%20dramatic.%20One%20Somali%20woman%20in%20Kenya%20told%20Mahla%3A%20%E2%80%9CThe%20climate%2C%20the%20drought%20and%20the%20weapons%20haven%E2%80%99t%20killed%20me%2C%20but%20I%20feel%20dead%20inside.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%202024%2C%20almost%20300%20million%20people%20worldwide%20will%20need%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fafrica-imf-sounds-alarm-on-declining-aid-rising-debt%2Fa-65330477%5C%22%3Ehumanitarian%20aid%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20Care%20International%20warned%2C%20almost%20half%20of%20them%20in%20Africa.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EDavid%20Mutua%20cites%20climate%20change%20as%20a%20decisive%20factor.%20From%20devastating%20droughts%20to%20extreme%20flooding%20%E2%80%94%20the%20continent%20suffers%20the%20most%20from%20climate%20change%2C%20even%20though%20it%20contributes%20the%20least%20to%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EWorldwide%2C%20humanitarian%20need%20has%20never%20been%20greater%20than%20in%202023.%20For%20Mahla%2C%20it%20is%20therefore%20not%20surprising%20that%20disasters%20in%20Africa%20receive%20too%20little%20attention%3A%20%E2%80%9CWe%20have%20experienced%20an%20unprecedented%20series%20of%20humanitarian%20crises%20and%20natural%20disasters%2C%E2%80%9D%20she%20says%2C%20referring%20to%20the%20earthquake%20in%20the%20Syrian-Turkish%20border%20region%2C%20floods%20in%20Libya%2C%20but%20also%20the%20wars%20in%20the%20Middle%20East%20and%20Ukraine.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3ECrises%20escalate%20in%20the%20shadow%20of%20crises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMany%20of%20the%20humanitarian%20crises%20in%20Africa%20would%20not%20make%20it%20into%20the%20news%20because%20they%20are%20all%20too%20familiar.%20They%20%E2%80%9Calready%20exist%2C%20sometimes%20they%20escalate%20in%20the%20shadow%20of%20the%20major%20crises%2C%E2%80%9D%20added%20Mahla.%20%E2%80%9CThere%20is%20nothing%20new%20to%20report%2C%20as%20sad%20as%20that%20sounds.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFor%20Fred%20Guilengue%2C%20fatigue%20over%20the%20numerous%20crises%20in%20Africa%20is%20a%20factor%20that%20inhibits%20attention%3A%20%E2%80%9CBut%20this%20tiredness%20has%20not%20just%20set%20in%20now%2C%20it%20already%20existed%20at%20the%20end%20of%20the%201990s%20and%20the%20beginning%20of%20the%202000s.%20Western%20countries%20were%20already%20tired%20of%20not%20seeing%20results%20when%20it%20came%20to%20democracy%20on%20the%20African%20continent%20and%20foreign%20aid%20in%20particular%2C%E2%80%9D%20he%20emphasised.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20addition%2C%20Deepmala%20Mahla%20notes%20that%20reporting%20from%20Africa%20is%20very%20expensive%20for%20foreign%20journalists%20and%20media%20groups.%20Many%20of%20these%20humanitarian%20crises%20are%20located%20in%20insecure%20regions%20that%20are%20subject%20to%20numerous%20restrictions%20imposed%20by%20governments%2C%20limiting%20access%20to%20these%20areas%20for%20journalists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOne%20such%20example%20is%20the%20Central%20African%20Republic.%20An%20armed%20conflict%20has%20been%20raging%20there%20since%202013%2C%20%E2%80%9Cwhich%20has%20repeatedly%20escalated%20and%20displaced%20families%20several%20times%2C%E2%80%9D%20says%20Deepmala%20Mahla%20from%20Care.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ETwenty%20percent%20of%20the%20population%20have%20been%20internally%20displaced%20or%20have%20fled%20to%20neighbouring%20countries.%20%E2%80%9CTwo-thirds%20of%20the%20population%2C%20more%20than%20three%20million%20people%2C%20have%20been%20in%20need%20of%20humanitarian%20aid%20for%20years%2C%E2%80%9D%20criticizes%20Mahla.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EPeople%20are%20tired%20of%20crises%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20Care%20International%2C%20there%20is%20also%20a%20lack%20of%20sufficient%20funding%20for%20humanitarian%20aid%20to%20save%20lives.%20In%202023%2C%20only%2035%25%20of%20the%20required%20financial%20resources%20were%20provided%20by%20donors.%20%E2%80%9CWe%20are%20also%20aware%20that%20people%20don%E2%80%99t%20want%20to%20or%20can%E2%80%99t%20consume%20news%20about%20disasters%20all%20the%20time%2C%20people%20are%20tired%20of%20crises%2C%E2%80%9D%20emphasised%20Mahla.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBetter%20cooperation%20with%20the%20media%20and%20politicians%20is%20necessary%20to%20bring%20such%20emergencies%20to%20the%20attention%20of%20the%20global%20public%2C%20she%20concluded.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EThis%20article%20was%20originally%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.dw.com%2Fen%2Fafricas-crises-fall-out-of-focus-as-global-attention-drifts%2Fa-67965128%5C%22%3Epublished%3C%2Fa%3E%20on%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3EDW.%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705317742000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15164502%2Fimage-1745.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fafricas-crises-fall-out-of-focus-as-global-attention-drifts%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Care%20International%20has%20listed%20the%20ten%20forgotten%20humanitarian%20crises%20of%20last%20year%20%E2%80%94%20all%20of%20them%20in%20Africa.%20Climate%20change%20plays%20a%20huge%20role%2C%20the%20aid%20organisation%20says%2C%20and%20more%20media%20attention%20is%20needed.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A5%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Fworld%2Fafricas-crises-fall-out-of-focus-as-global-attention-drifts%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Hostages%20seen%20in%20Hamas%20video%20as%20White%20House%20urges%20Israel%20to%20scale%20back%20offensive%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705317480000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fe3.365dm.com%2F24%2F01%2F768x432%2Fskynews-hostage-israel_6422266.jpg%3F20240115122616%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fhostages-seen-in-hamas-video-as-white-house-urges-israel-to-scale-back-offensive-13048873%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Hamas%20has%20aired%20a%20video%20of%20three%20Israeli%20hostages%20it%20is%20holding%20in%20Gaza%2C%20urging%20Israel%20to%20halt%20its%20offensive%20and%20bring%20about%20their%20release.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A261%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Fhostages-seen-in-hamas-video-as-white-house-urges-israel-to-scale-back-offensive-13048873%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews-sky-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fhostages-seen-in-hamas-video-as-white-house-urges-israel-to-scale-back-offensive-13048873%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fnews.sky.com%2Fstory%2Famp%2Fhostages-seen-in-hamas-video-as-white-house-urges-israel-to-scale-back-offensive-13048873%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22How%20SC's%20Latest%20Verdict%20Involving%20ED%20Eases%20Arrests%2C%20Bypassing%20Binding%20Law%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29180215%2FThe-Wire-1.png%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20month%2C%20the%20Supreme%20Court%20delivered%20its%20judgment%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2023%2F40323%2F40323_2023_15_1501_49103_Judgement_15-Dec-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3ERam%20Kishor%20Arora%20v.%20Directorate%20of%20Enforcement%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20indicating%20that%20its%20prior%20judgment%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fmain.sci.gov.in%2Fsupremecourt%2F2023%2F30275%2F30275_2023_16_1501_47281_Judgement_03-Oct-2023.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EPankaj%20Bansal%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20mandated%20the%20furnishing%20of%20written%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20to%20an%20accused%20at%20the%20moment%20of%20arrest%20by%20the%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20(ED)%20%E2%80%93%20was%20wrong%2C%20and%20that%20such%20grounds%20can%20be%20communicated%20orally%20at%20the%20moment%20of%20arrest%2C%20given%20their%20written%20furnishing%20in%20the%20next%2024%20hours.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20this%20essay%2C%20I%20discuss%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20reasoning%20in%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20proposing%20that%20its%20unjustified%20circumvention%20of%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20alongside%20its%20unclear%20stance%20on%20the%20implications%20of%20%3Cem%3EBansal%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20circumvention%2C%20means%20that%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20continues%20to%20govern%20the%20law%20on%20arbitrary%20arrests%2C%20with%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E%20requiring%20reconsideration%20by%20a%20larger%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3ER.K.%20Arora%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20Bypassing%20procedure%2C%20settled%20case-law%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20instant%20case%20arose%20with%20the%20ED%20arresting%20R.K.%20Arora%20%E2%80%93%20the%20founder%20of%20the%20real%20estate%20company%20Supertech%20Ltd.%20%E2%80%93%20concerning%20various%20allegations%20of%20the%20money%20laundering%20offence%2C%20which%20the%20ED%20is%20empowered%20to%20investigate%20and%20pursue%20under%20the%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fbitstream%2F123456789%2F2036%2F3%2FAA2003-15.pdf%5C%22%3EPrevention%20of%20Money%20Laundering%20Act%2C%202002%3C%2Fa%3E%20(PMLA).%20He%20had%20been%20previously%20summoned%20for%20interrogation%20by%20the%20ED%20u%2F%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F1395568%2F%5C%22%3Es%2050%20of%20the%20PMLA%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20connection%20with%20various%20offences%20constituting%20money%20laundering%2C%20for%20which%20he%20was%20arrested%20in%20June%202023.%20The%20ED%20can%2C%20in%20the%20exercise%20of%20its%20powers%20u%2Fs%2019%20of%20the%20PMLA%2C%20make%20arrests%20%E2%80%93%20a%20scheme%20upheld%20by%20the%20court%20in%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.livelaw.in%2Fpdf_upload%2F633-vijay-madanlal-choudhary-v-union-of-india-27-july-2022-428134.pdf%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EVijay%20Madanlal%20Choudhary%20v.%20Union%20of%20India%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAfter%20Arora%E2%80%99s%20bail%20applications%20were%20rejected%2C%20it%20was%20claimed%20that%20the%20arrest%20itself%20was%20vitiated%2C%20for%20the%20ED%20did%20not%20furnish%20its%20grounds%20in%20a%20written%20format%20at%20the%20time%20of%20making%20the%20arrest.%20The%20requirement%20of%20furnishing%20written%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20at%20the%20time%20the%20arrest%20is%20made%20(the%20%E2%80%9Cimmediate-furnishing%20rule%E2%80%9D)%20was%20read%20into%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fshow-data%3Factid%3DAC_CEN_2_2_00035_200315_1517807326550%26orderno%3D22%5C%22%3ESection%2019(1)%3C%2Fa%3E%20of%20the%20PMLA%20in%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20laid%20down%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0as%20I%20have%20argued%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fpankaj-bansal-verdict-valuable-step-basic-procedural-rights-applicable-ed%5C%22%3Ehere%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0three%20principles%3A%20first%2C%20the%20accused%20must%20%E2%80%93%20at%20the%20time%20of%20arrest%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0receive%20its%20grounds%20in%20a%20written%20format%3B%20second%2C%20that%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20general%20uncooperativeness%20during%20investigation%20cannot%20be%20a%20mode%20through%20which%20the%20agency%E2%80%99s%20%E2%80%9Creason%20to%20believe%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20guilt%20is%20developed%3B%20and%20third%2C%20that%20the%20ED%20cannot%20arrest%20with%20mala%20fides.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fed-grounds-of-arrest-writing-accused-within-24-supreme-court%5C%22%3EED%20Can%20Give%20Grounds%20in%20Writing%20To%20Accused%20Within%2024%20Hours%20of%20Arrest%3A%20Supreme%20Court%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20the%20first%20principle%20%E2%80%93%20which%20concerns%20the%20immediate%20furnishing%20rule%20%E2%80%93%20was%20alleged%20to%20have%20been%20violated.%20In%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20court%20held%20that%20if%20arrests%20are%20made%20without%20the%20fulfillment%20of%20the%20procedural%20condition%20of%20furnishing%20written%20grounds%2C%20the%20arrest%20would%20be%20vitiated%2C%20entitling%20the%20accused%20to%20an%20unconditional%20release.%20On%20this%20basis%2C%20Arora%20claimed%20that%20the%20non-furnishing%20of%20grounds%20at%20the%20moment%20of%20arrest%20entitled%20him%20to%20be%20released%2C%20notwithstanding%20that%20such%20grounds%20were%20furnished%20later.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20justifying%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20actions%20in%20effecting%20Arora%E2%80%99s%20arrest%2C%20the%20court%20bypassed%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0it%20held%20that%20the%20immediate-furnishing%20rule%20was%20unnecessary%2C%20and%20such%20grounds%20could%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0pursuant%20to%20the%20three-judge%20bench%20decision%20in%20%3Cem%3EChoudhary%20%3C%2Fem%3E%E2%80%93%20be%20furnished%20to%20the%20accused%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20may%20be%E2%80%9D.%20In%20interpreting%20this%20term%2C%20the%20court%20offered%20it%20the%20meaning%20%E2%80%9Cas%20early%20as%20possible%20without%20avoidable%20delay%E2%80%9D%2C%20or%20%E2%80%9Cwithin%20reasonably%20convenient%20or%20reasonably%20requisite%20period%20of%20time%E2%80%9D.%20This%20duration%2C%20in%20quantifiable%20terms%2C%20was%20capped%20at%2024%20hours%20after%20the%20arrest%3A%20this%20meant%20that%20while%20the%20accused%20is%20provided%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20orally%20at%20the%20moment%20of%20effecting%20arrest%2C%20the%20written%20grounds%20can%20be%20supplied%20within%20the%20next%2024%20hours%20(the%20%E2%80%9Cpostponement%20rule%E2%80%9D).%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EArora%E2%80%99s%20%3C%2Fem%3Edemerits%2C%20unjustified%20departures%20from%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20judgment%2C%20however%2C%20offers%20little%20justification%20for%20why%20this%20departure%20from%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20which%20was%20also%20a%20two-judge%20bench%20%E2%80%93%20is%20warranted.%20This%20is%20because%20under%20the%20system%20of%20%3Cem%3Estare%20decisis%2C%3C%2Fem%3E%20the%20court%20cannot%20depart%20from%20the%20law%20declared%20by%20a%20coordinate%20bench%2C%20and%20is%20bound%20irrespective%20of%20its%20disagreements%20therewith.%20The%20one%20exception%20to%20this%20norm%20is%20when%20the%20court%20finds%20the%20law%20declared%20by%20a%20coordinate%20bench%20%E2%80%9Cper%20incuriam%E2%80%9D%2C%20meaning%20that%20it%20ignored%20or%20departed%20from%20a%20binding%20precedent%2C%20decided%20by%20another%20coordinate%20or%20larger%20bench.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20insinuates%2C%20without%20conclusively%20observing%2C%20that%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%20in%20its%20pronouncement%20of%20the%20immediate-furnishing%20rule%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0departed%20from%20%3Cem%3EChoudhary%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20holding%20that%20%E2%80%9Cany%20observation%E2%80%A6contrary%20to%E2%80%A6Vijay%20Madanlal%20Choudhary%E2%80%A6would%20be%20not%20in%20consonance%20with%E2%80%A6jurisprudential%20wisdom%E2%80%9D.%20It%20does%20not%2C%20however%2C%20demonstrate%20how%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20undermines%20or%20deviates%20from%20%3Cem%3EChoudhary%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20court%20%E2%80%93%20in%20order%20to%20ward%20off%20possible%20criticism%20concerning%20its%20departure%20from%20%3Cem%3EChoudhary%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0specifically%20noted%20the%20extent%20to%20which%20%3Cem%3EChoudhary%3C%2Fem%3E%20applied%20to%20the%20issue%20of%20the%20police%E2%80%99s%20responsibilities%20while%20arresting%2C%20ensuring%20that%20its%20creation%20of%20the%20immediate-furnishing%20rule%20would%20not%20be%20deemed%20per%20incuriam%20in%20the%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20the%20court%20noted%20that%20%3Cem%3EChoudhary%3C%2Fem%3E%20went%20only%20insofar%20as%20suggesting%20that%20the%20accused%20must%20be%20informed%20of%20the%20arrest%E2%80%99s%20grounds%2C%20leaving%20open%20the%20question%20of%20the%20manner%20of%20communication.%20Based%20on%20%3Cem%3EChoudhary%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20silence%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20court%20held%20that%20the%20immediate-furnishing%20rule%20would%20best%20serve%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20interests%20%E2%80%93%20along%20with%2C%20but%20secondarily%2C%20those%20of%20the%20ED%20%E2%80%93%20for%20four%20reasons%3A%20first%2C%20the%20accused%2C%20in%20order%20to%20apply%20for%20bail%2C%20must%20know%20the%20circumstances%20leading%20to%20their%20arrest%2C%20necessitating%20their%20knowledge%20of%20the%20arrest%E2%80%99s%20grounds%3B%20second%2C%20since%20the%20ED%20has%20%E2%80%9Cmaterial%20in%E2%80%A6possession%E2%80%9D%20indicative%20of%20guilt%20as%20a%20precondition%20for%20arresting%20u%2Fs%2019(1)%2C%20an%20obligation%20to%20provide%20written%20grounds%20poses%20no%20disproportionate%20burden%3B%20third%2C%20permitting%20the%20furnishing%20of%20grounds%20orally%2C%20while%20simultaneously%20recognising%20that%20the%20arrest%20is%20vitiated%20based%20on%20their%20non-furnishing%2C%20meant%20that%20the%20only%20evidence%20in%20assessing%20vitiation%20would%20be%20%E2%80%9Cthe%20debatable%20ipse%20dixit%20of%20the%20authorized%20officer%E2%80%9D%3B%20and%20fourth%2C%20a%20person%20being%20arrested%20%E2%80%93%20due%20to%20the%20voluminous%20nature%20of%20the%20grounds%20and%20their%20anxious%20mental%20state%20%E2%80%93%20would%20be%20unable%20to%20remember%2C%20and%20consequently%20seek%20legal%20assistance%20in%20connection%20with%20the%20grounds%20orally%20disclosed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20however%2C%20the%20Court%20did%20not%20engage%20with%20these%20reasons%20favouring%20the%20immediate-furnishing%20rule%2C%20emphasising%20instead%20on%20a%20literal%20construction%20of%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20may%20be%E2%80%9D%20u%2Fs%2019(1)%2C%20which%20would%20%E2%80%93%20instead%20of%20implying%20an%20instant%20written%20furnishing%20of%20grounds%20%E2%80%93%20imply%20that%20such%20grounds%20be%20furnished%20within%2024%20hours.%20Simultaneously%2C%20however%2C%20the%20court%20remarked%20that%20the%20oral%20furnishing%20of%20grounds%20is%20essential%20at%20the%20moment%20of%20arrest.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThis%20restores%20the%20very%20same%20problem%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20sought%20to%20eliminate%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0now%2C%20challenges%20based%20on%20the%20vitiation%20of%20arrests%20due%20to%20non-furnishing%20of%20oral%20grounds%20at%20the%20moment%20of%20arrest%20can%20again%20be%20made%2C%20and%20the%20only%20evidence%20presentable%20by%20the%20ED%20and%20the%20accused%20%E2%80%93%20as%20noted%20in%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0becomes%20their%20ipse%20dixit.%20Further%2C%20the%20creation%20of%20the%20postponement%20rule%20is%20likely%20to%20act%20to%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20disadvantage%20at%20remand%20hearings%3A%20since%20the%20accused%20is%2C%20pursuant%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fshow-data%3Factid%3DAC_CEN_2_2_00035_200315_1517807326550%26orderno%3D22%5C%22%3ESection%2019(3)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20required%20to%20be%20presented%20before%20a%20Magistrate%20in%20twenty-four%20hours%2C%20they%20must%20be%20in%20a%20position%20to%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0pursuant%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F2982624%2F%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EArnesh%20Kumar%20v.%20State%20of%20Bihar%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0make%20a%20case%20for%20bail%20at%20the%20remand%20hearing%20itself.%20At%20the%20remand%20hearing%2C%20therefore%2C%20it%20is%20possible%20that%20the%20accused%20has%20not%20yet%20been%20furnished%20the%20written%20grounds%2C%20which%20places%20them%20in%20a%20situation%20where%20they%20must%20offer%20a%20legal%20defence%20without%20knowledge%20of%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20case%20against%20them.%20This%20is%20aggravated%20by%20the%20fact%20that%20bail%20under%20the%20PMLA%20is%20highly%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Findiankanoon.org%2Fdoc%2F873452%2F%5C%22%3Efactual%3C%2Fa%3E%20%E2%80%93%20the%20Magistrate%20assesses%20the%20likelihood%20with%20which%20an%20accused%20committed%20the%20offence%2C%20instead%20of%20enquiring%20into%20risks%20associated%20with%20release%2C%20such%20as%20tampering%20with%20evidence%2C%20intimidating%20witnesses%2C%20or%20fleeing.%20The%20accused%2C%20therefore%2C%20must%20know%20the%20collection%20of%20facts%20constituting%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20case%20in%20order%20to%20make%20a%20meaningful%20case%20at%20the%20remand%20hearing%2C%20an%20outcome%20made%20highly%20difficult%20by%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cins%3EAlso%20read%3A%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fenforcement-directorate-chhattisgarh-liquor-scam-overreach%5C%22%3E%E2%80%98Isn%E2%80%99t%20it%20Overreach%3F%E2%80%99%3A%20SC%20Hauls%20Up%20Enforcement%20Directorate%20Over%20%E2%80%98Hurry%E2%80%99%20in%20Arrests%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fins%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ELastly%2C%20even%20if%20the%20principled%20basis%20for%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E%20concerns%20the%20prevention%20of%20release-related%20litigation%20on%20frivolous%20grounds%20when%20the%20ED%20has%20%E2%80%93%20in%20substance%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0effectively%20communicated%20the%20reasons%20necessitating%20arrest%2C%20the%20additional%20burden%20imposed%20on%20the%20ED%20through%20the%20immediate-furnishing%20requirement%20is%20unclear.%20The%20ED%20must%2C%20pursuant%20to%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.indiacode.nic.in%2Fshow-data%3Factid%3DAC_CEN_2_2_00035_200315_1517807326550%26orderno%3D22%5C%22%3ESection%2019(1)%3C%2Fa%3E%2C%20record%20its%20%E2%80%9Creason%20to%20believe%E2%80%9D%20in%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20guilt%20in%20a%20written%20form%20before%20an%20arrest%20is%20made.%20In%20case%20the%20ED%20is%20already%20in%20possession%20of%20a%20written%20document%20containing%20the%20reasons%20through%20which%20its%20belief%20in%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20guilt%20has%20been%20developed%2C%20it%20is%20unclear%20how%20the%20furnishing%20of%20such%20reasons%20at%20the%20time%20of%20arrest%20is%20a%20burdensome%20task%2C%20such%20that%20the%20case-law%20has%20to%20be%20dubiously%20modified%20to%20give%20the%20ED%20an%20additional%20day%20to%20do%20it.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3E%3Cem%3EBansal%20%3C%2Fem%3Enot%20overruled%2C%20continues%20to%20govern%20the%20law%20on%20arrests%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20departure%20from%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20aside%2C%20the%20court%20in%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E%20is%20highly%20unclear%20in%20its%20own%20conceptualization%20of%20the%20implications%20of%20its%20disagreement%20with%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E.%20As%20an%20aside%2C%20it%20must%20be%20noted%20that%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20offered%20three%20principles%20governing%20the%20ED%E2%80%99s%20power%20of%20arrest%2C%20and%20two%20of%20them%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0which%20concern%20the%20prohibition%20on%20arresting%20with%20mala%20fides%2C%20and%20the%20prohibition%20on%20the%20%E2%80%9Creason%20to%20believe%E2%80%9D%20u%2Fs%2019(1)%20developing%20through%20the%20accused%E2%80%99s%20uncooperativeness%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0continue%20to%20be%20the%20law%2C%20irrespective%20of%20%3Cem%3EArora%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20legal%20effects.%20The%20only%20issue%20on%20which%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E%20could%20have%20departed%20from%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20the%20immediate-furnishing%20rule%2C%20which%2C%20I%20propose%2C%20also%20continues%20to%20be%20the%20law.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EArora%2C%20the%20accused%20in%20the%20instant%20case%2C%20was%20arrested%20in%20June%202023%2C%20while%20the%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20delivered%20in%20October%202023.%20The%20Court%2C%20in%20holding%20that%20the%20ED%20had%20no%20obligation%20to%20provide%20Mr.%20Arora%20the%20written%20grounds%20of%20his%20arrest%2C%20held%20that%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20did%20not%20operate%20retrospectively%2C%20for%20it%20used%20the%20word%20%E2%80%9Chenceforth%E2%80%9D%20in%20qualifying%20the%20written-grounds%20requirement.%20On%20this%20basis%2C%20the%20non-furnishing%20of%20grounds%20till%20the%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20was%20upheld%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%2223%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%E2%80%9C%E2%80%A6The%20submission%E2%80%A6that%20the%20said%20judgment%20%5B%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%5D%20was%20required%20to%20be%20given%20effect%20retrospectively%20cannot%20be%20accepted%20when%20the%20judgment%20itself%20states%20that%20it%20would%20be%20necessary%20%E2%80%9Chenceforth%E2%80%9D%20that%20a%20copy%20of%20such%20written%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20is%20furnished%E2%80%A6%3Cu%3EHence%20non%20furnishing%20of%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20in%20writing%20till%20the%20date%20of%20pronouncement%20of%20judgment%20in%20Pankaj%20Bansal%20case%20could%20neither%20be%20held%20to%20be%20illegal%3C%2Fu%3E%20nor%20the%20action%20of%20the%20concerned%20officer%20in%20not%20furnishing%20the%20same%20in%20writing%20could%20be%20faulted%20with.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EBased%20on%20the%20prospective%20character%20of%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20therefore%2C%20the%20Court%20held%20that%20the%20non-furnishing%20of%20written%20grounds%20to%20Mr.%20Arora%20could%20not%20be%20considered%20illegal.%20Simultaneously%2C%20however%2C%20the%20Court%20moved%20from%20the%20immediate-furnishing%20rule%20to%20the%20postponement%20rule%2C%20holding%20that%20such%20a%20construction%20would%20do%20justice%20to%20the%20term%20%E2%80%9Cas%20soon%20as%20may%20be%E2%80%9D%20u%2Fs%2019(1)%2C%20as%20it%20was%20interpreted%20in%20%3Cem%3EChoudhary%3C%2Fem%3E%3A%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%2222%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%E2%80%9CTherefore%2C%20in%20our%20opinion%20the%20person%20asserted%2C%20%3Cu%3Eif%20he%20is%20informed%20or%20made%20aware%20orally%20about%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20at%20the%20time%20of%20his%20arrest%20and%20is%20furnished%20a%20written%20communication%20about%20the%20grounds%20of%20arrest%20as%20soon%20as%20may%20be%20i.e%20as%20early%20as%20possible%20and%20within%20reasonably%20convenient%20and%20requisite%20time%20of%20twenty-four%20hours%20of%20his%20arrest%2C%20that%20would%20be%20sufficient%20compliance%3C%2Fu%3E%20of%20not%20only%20Section%2019%20of%20PMLA%20but%20also%20of%20Article%2022(1)%20of%20the%20Constitution%20of%20India.%E2%80%9D%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20above%20holding%2C%20it%20is%20submitted%2C%20is%20per%20incuriam%2C%20for%20it%20wholly%20conflicts%20with%20%3Cem%3EBansal%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20pronouncement%20on%20the%20very%20same%20legal%20question%20without%20finding%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20itself%20bad%20in%20law.%20The%20postponement%20rule%20has%20the%20effect%20of%20displacing%20the%20immediate-furnishing%20rule%20laid%20down%20in%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20and%20the%20two%20cannot%20coexist.%20The%20only%20correct%20reading%20of%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20therefore%2C%20is%20one%20that%20constrains%20its%20application%20to%20arrests%20prior%20to%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20such%20that%20the%20oral%20furnishing%20of%20grounds%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0alongside%20a%20postponed%20delivery%20of%20written%20grounds%20%E2%80%93%C2%A0would%20not%20have%20the%20effect%20of%20vitiating%20an%20arrest%20(provided%2C%20of%20course%2C%20its%20occurrence%20prior%20to%20%3Cem%3EBansal)%3C%2Fem%3E.%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E%20would%2C%20therefore%2C%20require%20reconsideration%2C%20so%20that%20the%20postponement%20rule%20becomes%20confined%20in%20application%20to%20pre-%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20arrests%2C%20and%20the%20immediate-furnishing%20rule%20for%20post-%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20arrests%20is%20affirmed.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EConclusion%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20this%20basis%2C%20I%20submit%20that%20the%20court%E2%80%99s%20judgment%20in%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E%2C%20which%20offers%20highly%20lacklustre%20reasoning%20in%20departing%20from%20%3Cem%3EBansal%E2%80%99s%3C%2Fem%3E%20immediate-furnishing-rule%2C%20is%20also%20per%20incuriam%20to%20the%20extent%20it%20seeks%20to%20replace%20the%20immediate-furnishing%20rule%20with%20the%20postponement%20rule%20for%20post-%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E%20cases.%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E%20can%20be%20offered%20only%20one%20correct%20reading%2C%20such%20that%20its%20application%20is%20constrained%20to%20cases%20where%20the%20ED%20made%20arrests%20prior%20to%20%3Cem%3EBansal%3C%2Fem%3E.%20In%20order%20to%20prevent%20the%20attribution%20of%20precedential%20value%20to%20the%20postponement%20rule%2C%20%3Cem%3EArora%3C%2Fem%3E%20must%20be%20reconsidered%20in%20the%20near%20future.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cem%3EKartik%20Kalra%20is%20a%20third-year%20B.A.%20LLB%20(Hons)%20student%20at%20the%20National%20Law%20School%20of%20India%20University%20Bengaluru.%C2%A0%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1705317057000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2023%2F08%2F29180215%2FThe-Wire-1.png%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fhow-scs-latest-verdict-involving-ed-eases-arrests-bypassing-binding-law%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22The%20top%20court%E2%80%99s%20verdict%20is%20unjustified%20in%20the%20sense%20that%20it%20offers%20highly%20lacklustre%20reasoning%20in%20departing%20from%20the%20previous%20%E2%80%98immediate-furnishing-rule%E2%80%99%2C%20where%20the%20person%20about%20to%20get%20arrested%20was%20given%20in%20writing%20the%20grounds%20for%20their%20arrest.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A20%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fthewire.in%2Flaw%2Fhow-scs-latest-verdict-involving-ed-eases-arrests-bypassing-binding-law%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22In%20Photos%3A%20The%20Road%20to%20the%20Ganga%20Sagar%20Mela%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15155954%2FKochuberia-Sagor-jatri-4-1.jpg%5C%22%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20annual%20Ganga%20Sagar%20Mela%20is%20currently%20underway%20at%20Sagar%20Dwip%20in%20West%20Bengal.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAccording%20to%20the%20South%2024%20Parganas%20district%20administration%2C%20the%20Mela%2C%20which%20began%20on%20Monday%20and%20will%20go%20on%20till%20January%2017%2C%20has%20drawn%20approximately%206.5%20million%20pilgrims%20and%20tourists.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cimg%20sizes%3D%5C%22(max-width%3A%20709px)%2085vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%20909px)%2067vw%2C%20(max-width%3A%201362px)%2062vw%2C%20840px%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fcdn.thewire.in%2Fwp-content%2Fuploads%2F2024%2F01%2F15160227%2FKochuberia-Sagor-jatri-1-1-1.jpg%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20width%3D%5C%221200%5C%22%20srcset%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fc